    <h1 class="center">U. S. Department of Commerce, U. S. Census Bureau</h1>
    
    <h2 class="center">           X-13ARIMA-SEATS monthly regARIMA model estimation Method, <br> 
    Release Version 1.1 Build 61</h2>
    
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="center">This software application provides an enhanced version of
<br> Statistics Canada's X-11-ARIMA extension (Dagum, 1980)
 <br> of the X-11 variant of the Census Method II of
 <br> Shiskin, Young and Musgrave (1967).</p>

<p class="center">It also provides an ARIMA model-based method following
 <br> Hillmer and Tiao (1982) and Burman (1980) that is very similar
 <br> to the update of the method of SEATS (<span lang="es">G&oacute;mez</span> and Maravall, 1996)
 <br> produced at the Bank of Spain by G. Caporello and
 <br> A. Maravall for TSW (Caporello and Maravall, 2004).
 <br> The present application includes additional enhancements.</p>

<p class="center">X-13ARIMA-SEATS includes an automatic ARIMA model selection procedure
 <br> based largely on the procedure of <span lang="es">G&oacute;mez</span> and <span lang="es">Maravall</span> (1998)
 <br> as implemented in TRAMO (1996) and subsequent revisions.</p>

<p class="center">Primary Programmers: Brian Monsell, Mark Otto and,
 <br> for the ARIMA model-based signal extraction,
 <br> <span lang="it">Gianluca Caporello</span> and 
<span lang="es">V&iacute;ctor G&oacute;mez</span></p>

<tr><th scope="row"> <abbr title="Akaike information criterion">AIC</abbr></th><td>                                519.8862  </td></tr>
<tr><th scope="row"> <abbr title="corrected Akaike information criterion">AICC</abbr> (F-corrected-<abbr title="Akaike information criterion">AIC</abbr>)</th><td>                                520.5862  </td></tr>
<tr><th scope="row"> Hannan Quinn </th><td>                                526.8195  </td></tr>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
 <hr> 
<p>nobs   = number of observations <br> 
 nefobs = nobs  - total order of differencing operators <br> 
 np     = number of estimated regression and ARIMA model
            parameters including the variance <br> 
 V      = Covariance matrix of z's <br> 
    z      = Vector of data - regression values <br> 
    c      = Vector of prior adjustment factors <br> 
    Log likelihood =
    -[nefobs*log(2*pi)+log|V|+z'(V-inverse)z]/2 <br> 
 Transformation Adjustment = sum(ln(|(ci*(ci*yi)^(lam-1))|))
 where the sum is over the last nefobs observations <br> 
 <abbr title="Akaike information criterion">AIC</abbr>

 = -2*L+2*np <br> 
 <abbr title="corrected Akaike information criterion">AICC</abbr> = -2*L+2*np*[nefobs/(nefobs-np-1)] <br> 
 Hannan Quinn = -2*L+2*np*log[log(nefobs)] <br> 
 <abbr title="Bayesian information criterion">BIC</abbr> = -2*L+np*log(nefobs)</p>

<p class="center">***** <abbr title="corrected Akaike information criterion">AICC</abbr>
 (with aicdiff=-2.00) prefers <strong>log transformation</strong> *****</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
 <hr> 
<p>nobs   = number of observations <br> 
 nefobs = nobs  - total order of differencing operators <br> 
 np     = number of estimated regression and ARIMA model
            parameters including the variance <br> 
 V      = Covariance matrix of z's <br> 
          z      = Vector of data - regression values <br> 
          c      = Vector of prior adjustment factors <br> 
          Log likelihood =
          -[nefobs*log(2*pi)+log|V|+z'(V-inverse)z]/2 <br> 
 Transformation Adjustment = sum(ln(|(ci*(ci*yi)^(lam-1))|))
 where the sum is over the last nefobs observations <br> 
 <abbr title="Akaike information criterion">AIC</abbr>

 = -2*L+2*np <br> 
 <abbr title="corrected Akaike information criterion">AICC</abbr> = -2*L+2*np*[nefobs/(nefobs-np-1)] <br> 
 Hannan Quinn = -2*L+2*np*log[log(nefobs)] <br> 
 <abbr title="Bayesian information criterion">BIC</abbr> = -2*L+np*log(nefobs)</p>
